name: I Love Hip Hop
description:
A donation will be made to The DJ Kool Herc Foundation from each tee sold.
This is a doctored version of the iconic "I Love NY" tourism campaign. Changed to reflect a love for Hip Hop culture, with the heart rendered with a picture of the birthplace of Hip Hop, 1520 Sedgwick Avenue in the Bronx.

name: CCTV Stencil
description:
This design was originally a graffiti stencil thrown up when the keep calm and carry on merchandise first became popular,
but the obvious way this take on the image works on a tee was too good to pass up. 
Some-time graffiti artist Stray worked this doctored take on the iconic tee to make a statement on the UK becoming a Big Brother state.

Normally £20 Now just £15

name: Your Environment Needs You
description:
Made from organic threads, this t-shirt is a doctored take on the 'your country needs you' poster from the first world war. Graffiti artist Stray, originally thought of this a concept for a piece of street art. We decided that this design obviously works real nice on organic clothing.
As we build the foundations of our brand and grow as a company, we plan to sell only organic and fair trade clothing, until then this piece was perfect to start with.

Normally £25 now £20.

name: The Origin Tee
description:

name: Each One Teach One Tee
description:
The 8th Element of Hip Hop is knowledge and a many Hip Hop heads and groups like the Zulu Nation, have adopted the saying "Each One Teach One" and the message it states, spreading knowledge throughout the Hip Hop community. 

Originally an African-American Proverb from the days of slavery, When the slaves were denied education so took it upon themselves to teach each other any skills or knowledge they knew or learnt, giving birth to the saying "Each one teach one." 

We think in these days of biased; narrow minded, politically aligned, bigoted journalism and failing education systems, that this idea still holds weight and its message should be spread amongst open-minded people.

Normally £20 now on sale for £15
